Tweet text:
In case you missed it, we have 3 open opportunities: 
1⃣ Data Science Fellow
2⃣ Community Engagement and Outreach Coordinator
3⃣ Science Advisory Board Nominations

More info:
https://t.co/013H7GKLCY 

Please share widely!

The MEaSUREs #Greenland #Ice Mapping Project (GIMP) Land Ice and Ocean Classification Mask, Version 1 dataset has just been updated! Check out this dataset over at @NSIDC: https://t.co/2vJMly2cCz #SharingDataFriday https://t.co/Zva1MO76ay
Mark your calendars! We will be at the #ESA2021 #DataHelpDesk sessions Aug 2 - Aug 5 12 - 1 PST. Add them to your schedule here: https://t.co/O6c035equA

Some #GoodNewsTues: a #VirtualReality tour of the @MOSAiCArctic's ice camp is now available! Immerse yourself and your students in the #Arctic with this neat resource. https://t.co/tfl8XvrXre. https://t.co/jil2Odg3i0

Can changes in tall shrub extent within #Arctic #riparian corridors serve as bioindicators of changes in stream #hydrological and #biological functioning? Check out the paper here ▶️https://t.co/z8bGIhne9P Data: https://t.co/fiXBxCyYZB & https://t.co/TZkoUIqzD9 https://t.co/2tO6bNhIIy

New version available from @NSIDC! The MEaSUREs dataset, now on version 3, provides velocity estimates determined from Interferometric Synthetic Aperture Radar (InSAR) data for major #glacier outlet areas in Greenland. https://t.co/zPFZQZPIi0 #TechTuesday https://t.co/Tx7CydUJYh

The relationship between #Arctic sea #ice decline and #tundra vegetation is extremely uncertain. Read more about the complexities of Arctic sea ice dynamics and terrestrial systems here:  https://t.co/GnKOAebetW Data:  https://t.co/TJFgj22aM1 https://t.co/aqi1yhvWxC

#SharingSciFri: a #NewPaper by Rangel etc looks at #permafrost aggradation (deposition of sediment) under drained lake basins in #Alaska. Paper: https://t.co/3ycx9vvX9l Data: https://t.co/F7ssnVJBDL / https://t.co/I7NfRjomP6 / https://t.co/HBWnERzF8f https://t.co/n0nqZoDQ6U

Strap on your crampons and explore this paper that discusses open #crevasse depths and patterns in #Greenland! Crevasses are important in assessing rapid and long-term changes in stressors on #terrestrialice formations. Paper: https://t.co/80fBZqWpJp Data: https://t.co/1LJFaxCImS https://t.co/5BGRHoyUXK

#NewPaper from @WhovianVeganGeo uses #FAIRdata source @DataONEorg to contextualize historical landscape photographs alongside present-day datasets from fieldwork in similar places. Check it out: https://t.co/f2wBFOWamS & some of the data came from us: https://t.co/Od01MKnXZT https://t.co/DdoOlzyUKW

#NewPaper from @DrHeatherKropp et al: Shallow soils are warmer under trees and tall shrubs across Arctic and
Boreal ecosystems. Paper: https://t.co/hVwXVzAhpS Data: https://t.co/KnVXhRmf4N https://t.co/aKosnDBZKr

#WarmingWednesday: warming in the #Arctic releases gases, & while #permafrost & lake thawing has been studied extensively, stream thaw hasn't been. Read Harms et al: streams emit MORE methane & CO2 than expected (https://t.co/0fJbsxiJJk) & see data here (https://t.co/zw42BVzylr). https://t.co/73U4a1HTU8

#NewPaper: Comparisons of chemical compositions of glacial streams draining the #Greenland Ice Sheet and nearby non‐glacial streams document different amounts of #nutrients discharging from the landscapes. Read more: https://t.co/Fxin3gb6KL See #data: https://t.co/Ycz50t10ja https://t.co/86K4FtVf5V

Even in the remote #Arctic, seabirds ingest plastics...but there isn't much monitoring, so we don't know the full extent of the problem. Check out a new review by @baakjuliae that condenses 38 studies & calls for more research to be done! https://t.co/PJDO9wokOL https://t.co/Pd5FNxZAY3
